Project Folder Structure
ansible-nginx/
├── inventory.ini        # Target servers list
├── playbook.yml         # Main playbook
├── ansible.cfg          # Ansible configuration

📄 File 1: inventory.ini (Target Servers)
ini[webservers]
192.168.1.10 ansible_user=ubuntu ansible_ssh_private_key_file=~/.ssh/id_rsa

[webservers:vars]
ansible_python_interpreter=/usr/bin/python3

💡 Replace 192.168.1.10 with your target server's IP address


📄 File 2: ansible.cfg (Configuration)
ini[defaults]
inventory = inventory.ini
remote_user = ubuntu
host_key_checking = False

📄 File 3: playbook.yml (Main Playbook)
yaml---
- name: Install and Configure Nginx on Target Servers
  hosts: webservers
  become: yes        # Run as sudo/root

  vars:
    nginx_port: 80
    nginx_message: "Welcome to My Ansible Nginx Server!"

  tasks:

    - name: Update apt package manager
      apt:
        update_cache: yes

    - name: Install Nginx
      apt:
        name: nginx
        state: present

    - name: Start Nginx service
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started
        enabled: yes

    - name: Create custom index.html
      copy:
        content: "<h1>{{ nginx_message }}</h1>"
        dest: /var/www/html/index.html

    - name: Verify Nginx is running
      command: systemctl status nginx
      register: nginx_status

    - name: Print Nginx status
      debug:
        msg: "{{ nginx_status.stdout }}"

